<subSubSection id="C3436526FFA0FF9A29C9665AFB2EF82E" pageId="17" pageNumber="76" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BE636ADFFA0FF9A29C9665AFB2EF82E" blockId="17.[151,1437,1860,1921]" pageId="17" pageNumber="76">
<emphasis id="B92DEABFFFA0FF9A29C9665AFEB2F8F3" bold="true" box="[199,334,1860,1885]" pageId="17" pageNumber="76">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name refers to the slender feature of the aedeagus and the specific name is a Latin compound name: adjective stem 
<emphasis id="B92DEABFFFA0FF9A2B096677FDBEF82F" box="[519,578,1897,1921]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="76">petil-</emphasis>
(slender) + connective vowel 
<emphasis id="B92DEABFFFA0FF9A2A986677FC62F82E" box="[918,926,1897,1920]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="76">i</emphasis>
+ substantive 
<emphasis id="B92DEABFFFA0FF9A2D4F6677FB8AF82F" box="[1089,1142,1897,1921]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="76">colis</emphasis>
(penis).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
